Planet Earth Entry Timestamp 1981

I've been introducing my friends to music they haven't heard since I was a teenager. I'm from Rhode Island. My musical path has lead me through modern rock, drum and bass, late 90's trance, and into house/electronic music. Techno, minimal, prog, dare I say dubstep!? Genres aren't a very good way to classify music. I'd rather keep track of it by good production values. Clean highs - heavy bass - and a steady groove is what I'm looking for in a track. 

I started spinning electronic music in 99 with two turntables. Raves led to clubs. Twilo in NYC in particular was a turning point for me musically. Pulsating bass that rattled right through my lungs. High-hat loops that were crystal clear. And all the other frequencies that came out of the Phazon system certainly got the synapses firing. Since then I just want to mix beats and find the best combinations possible. I hope you enjoy my selections.

Da Moth has been pushing the limits in the bass music scene since the late 90s, ,playing massives and undergrounds all over New England and New York including legendary clubs like The Limelight, The Tunnel ,DKNY and The Asylum...

               In 2010, Da Moth solidified his place in the LA bass scene by becoming resident DJ not to mention sound engineer and tech for L.A.'s largest monthly basscentric event LA BEATDOWN. He has performed with legendary artist such as Nero,Feed Me,Q-Bert,Hive Borgore and has done sound for almost every prominent bass DJ in the game..

In 2015 Da Moth took some time off from his own music to tour the world as head sound engineer and Ableton tech for MTV artist of the year... Porter Robinsons' "WORLDS" tour.

        Recently Da Moth has been focused on his new venture, Being the COO and Label Manager for The Producers Social.. a monthly workshop for producers and vocalists to get together and share original music and receive feedback on their work and socialize. It has grown to 4 cities in the past year and has become one of the best industry nights drawing the most talented musicians..from headliners to newbies...
          
            Marks production style is a mash up of all his favorite genres...Dnb/Jungle, Dub,Trap, Breaks and Hip Hop with a flare of sexy weirdness to keep it all glued together...Not afraid to think outside the box and make music that doesn't fit into any one particular mold.

          As a DJ, Da Moth is known for being quite the crate digger..Always searching for that heater in buried in the dark corners of the interwebs.His open format bass style can rock the biggest stage at the festival or melt your head at a BRC sunrise set....Da Moth’s intense and original artistic vision is seemingly unlimited and he is always looking to grow and evolve.When it comes down to it it doesn’t matter if he is behind the decks, in the studio or running the sound, Da Moth is a force to be reckoned with. Artist, visionary, engineer,insane…. whatever you choose to call him, Da moth is simply by nature a cotton mouth madman set on destroy.Contact @ Mark@producerssocial.com
